abstract: Facing questions about his campaign's viability, Joe Biden escalated his criticism of his top Democratic rivals on Wednesday, suggesting both Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg were risky choices for a party desperate for a return to the White House.
snippet: Facing questions about his campaign's viability, Joe Biden escalated his criticism of his top Democratic rivals on Wednesday, suggesting both Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg were risky choices for a party desperate for a return to the White Hous...
lead_paragraph: SOMERSWORTH, N.H. — Facing questions about his campaign's viability, Joe Biden escalated his criticism of his top Democratic rivals on Wednesday, suggesting both Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg were risky choices for a party desperate for a return to the White House.
headline_main: Biden Casts Top Rivals as a Risk for Party That Wants to Win
headline_print_headline: Biden Casts Top Rivals as a Risk for Party That Wants to Win

abstract: The biggest winner, Mayor Pete, loses the most from the debacle, while a big loser, Biden, welcomed the absurdity.
snippet: The biggest winner, Mayor Pete, loses the most from the debacle, while a big loser, Biden, welcomed the absurdity.
lead_paragraph: The disaster in Iowa on Monday night exemplified so much about the American situation at the moment — the failure of our parties, the self-sabotage of our institutions, the disastrous interaction between creaking political systems and the flimflam “improvements” of the tech economy — that it’s tempting not to attempt political analysis at all and just let the thing stand as a kind of outrageous art installation, a fiasco that speaks for itself so completely that all commentary is superfluous.

abstract: WASHINGTON — Troy Price, the Iowa Democratic Party chairman, apologized for the Monday night debacle that led to a 20-hour delay in reporting results from the Iowa caucuses and said his party released results from 62 percent of precincts on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Troy Price, the Iowa Democratic Party chairman, apologized for the Monday night debacle that led to a 20-hour delay in reporting results from the Iowa caucuses and said his party released results from 62 percent of precincts on Tuesday.

headline_main: Everyone Kept Saying Politics Was Broken. Well?
headline_print_headline: A Debacle  That Adds  To Doubts About It All

abstract: A first wave of results showed Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders with an early lead, with Joseph R. Biden Jr. well behind.
snippet: A first wave of results showed Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders with an early lead, with Joseph R. Biden Jr. well behind.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Democratic officials in Iowa on Tuesday provided a measure of clarity to the muddled outcome of its statewide caucuses, releasing a delayed first wave of partial results that showed Pete Buttigieg and Senator Bernie Sanders with a preliminary lead and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. falling well behind the other top-tier candidates.

abstract: KEENE, N.H. — Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts called on the Iowa Democratic Party to “get it together,” saying the reporting errors that upended caucus results threatened to damage trust in the democratic process.
lead_paragraph: KEENE, N.H. — Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts called on the Iowa Democratic Party to “get it together,” saying the reporting errors that upended caucus results threatened to damage trust in the democratic process.
